        "title": "1. `models.py` — `parse_posted_at`, `Job`",
        "content": "\nHighest ROI: pure functions, no I/O, and `parse_posted_at` has three separate parsing branches (epoch-seconds, epoch-ms, ISO-8601) that are currently unverified.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Millisecond vs. second epoch disambiguation (`>= 1e12` threshold) — untested at the boundary.\n- Negative/garbage numeric strings (`\"-1\"`, `\"abc123\"`).\n- Trailing `Z` normalization for pre-3.11 `fromisoformat` compat.\n- Naive ISO strings (no tzinfo) — should get `UTC` attached.\n- Empty string / `None`-like input → `None`.\n- Workday's `\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"` prose → must return `None`, not raise.\n- `Job.key` stability across title/location edits (dedup identity).\n- `Job.content_hash` — verify it changes when title/location/url/department change, and does NOT change when e.g. `posted_at` or `salary_range` change (those are excluded from the hash — worth locking that in explicitly since it's a deliberate design choice with no comment/test backing it).\n- `Job.to_row()` drops `raw`, includes computed `key`/`content_hash`.\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 3
