        "title": "tests/test_fetchers_fetch_all.py",
        "content": "import httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_failures(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    def handler(request):\n        if \"broken\" in str(request.url):\n            return httpx.Response(500)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"X\",\n            \"absolute_url\": \"\", \"location\": {}, \"departments\": []}]})\n    transport = httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport)\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"broken\"},\n               {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"ok\"}]\n    jobs = await fetch_all(sources, client=client, concurrency=2)\n    await client.aclose()\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n    assert \"! greenhouse:broken failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises():\n    from fetchers import fetch_source\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n        await fetch_source(None, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n```\n\n**D. Pagination stop conditions** (`fetch_optiver`, `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_bytedance`, `fetch_apple`, `fetch_google`) — each has slightly different \"stop paginating\" logic (empty fresh batch, dedup-by-`external_id`, `max_pages` cap, or a `total`/`count` check). At minimum, test one representative fetcher for: (1) stops when a page returns no new items, (2) respects `max_pages`, (3) dedupes across pages when the API returns overlapping results. `fetch_google`'s `_extract_ds1` regex-based extraction is especially fragile (site-layout-shift risk) and deserves its own malformed-HTML test (missing `ds:1` key → `[]`, not a crash).\n\n**E. `fetch_ashby`'s fallback path** (posting-api 404 → hosted-page HTML scrape) is a distinct code path from the happy path and is entirely untested — needs a mocked 404 + a mocked HTML page with `window.__appData`.\n\n---\n\n",
