        "title": "5. `notify.py` — notifiers + `dispatch`",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:**\n- Each notifier's env-var gating: absent env var → no-op, no network call attempted (verify via `monkeypatch.delenv` + asserting no httpx call).\n- Each notifier's \"nothing to report\" short-circuit (`not (new or changed)`).\n- `dispatch()`'s exception isolation — **currently the single most important untested behavior in this file**: if `notify_slack` raises (e.g., bad webhook), `notify_email`/`notify_sms` must still run. There's no test proving this.\n- `_sms_body`: truncation at `limit`, ASCII-only content (no `•`/`…`), `\"+N more\"` suffix.\n- `notify_sms`: `raise_for_status()` propagates on Twilio failure (and `dispatch` must swallow it, per above).\n\n```python\n",
