        "content": "import pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, main\n\ndef test_db_mark_rejects_invalid_timestamp(capsys):\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\"])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\ndef test_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(capsys):\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_replaces_body_text_only():\n    html = '<style>content: \"\\u2014\";</style><p>em\\u2014dash</p>'\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'content: \"\\u2014\"' in out  # untouched inside <style>\n    assert \"em-dash\" in out            # replaced in body\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_does_not_touch_tag_attributes():\n    html = '<a title=\"quote\\u2019s\">text</a>'\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'title=\"quote\\u2019s\"' in out  # attribute preserved\n    assert counts == {}\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_counts_multiple_replacement_types():\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>a\\u2014b \\u201Cquoted\\u201D c\\u2026</p>\")\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n    assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n    assert counts[\"ellipsis\"] == 1\n\ndef test_main_help_flag(capsys):\n    rc = main.__wrapped__([\"-h\"]) if hasattr(main, \"__wrapped__\") else None\n    # or invoke via subprocess if main() reads sys.argv directly\n```\n\n(`main()` reads `sys.argv` directly rather than taking an `argv` param, so testing it cleanly requires either a small refactor to accept `argv` — recommended — or `monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [...])` + capturing `SystemExit`/return code.)\n\nFor `cmd_db_new`'s truncation logic specifically:\n\n```python\ndef test_db_new_truncates_at_group_boundary_not_mid_group(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    # Build a store with two first_seen groups of 3 rows each, limit=4.\n    # Assert the dump contains exactly 3 rows (first full group only),\n    # watermark == first group's timestamp — proves it never splits a group.\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n",
